WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:09.274
<i>Previously on the affair...</i>

2
00:00:09.309 --> 00:00:11.142
Welcome to the end of the world.

3
00:00:11.177 --> 00:00:12.521
<i>Do you remember
the first time you saw her?</i>

4
00:00:12.545 --> 00:00:14.279
<i>Like it was yesterday.</i>

5
00:00:14.314 --> 00:00:15.747
I'm noah. by the way.

6
00:00:15.782 --> 00:00:16.848
What are we talking about?

7
00:00:16.883 --> 00:00:18.116
Noah's new book.

8
00:00:18.151 --> 00:00:19.417
Great. I didn't know.

9
00:00:19.452 --> 00:00:20.285
There was enough
to talk about yet.

10
00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:21.786
<i>Well.</i>

11
00:00:21.821 --> 00:00:22.999
<i>I haven't really gotten
too far with it.</i>

12
00:00:23.023 --> 00:00:24.023
<i>Is she flirting with you?</i>

13
00:00:24.057 --> 00:00:25.297
Do you want to get out of here?

14
00:00:26.393 --> 00:00:28.493
I don't want to divorce you.
you asshole!

15
00:00:28.528 --> 00:00:30.495
What... what do you want?

16
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:32.997
I want you to come home.

17
00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:34.299
<i>It's extraordinary.</i>

18
00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:36.200
I want it in stores
by next fall.

19
00:00:36.236 --> 00:00:37.602
<i>I don't want this life.</i>

20
00:00:37.637 --> 00:00:39.437
<i>I have to leave.</i>

21
00:00:39.472 --> 00:00:40.805
<i>I'm in love with someone else.</i>

22
00:00:40.840 --> 00:00:42.140
You have chosen to divorce.

23
00:00:42.175 --> 00:00:44.676
In what I like to call
a humane way.

24
00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:46.844
<i>I blew up my life
for you. alison.</i>

25
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.012
I don't belong to you.

26
00:00:48.048 --> 00:00:49.013
We're not living in your book.

27
00:00:49.049 --> 00:00:51.015
You can't... Control me.

28
00:00:55.055 --> 00:00:56.321
I'm pregnant.

29
00:00:58.091 --> 00:00:59.857
I don't know
who joanie's father is.

30
00:00:59.893 --> 00:01:01.659
I never want to see you again.

31
00:01:01.695 --> 00:01:03.528
And I thought
she had done it deliberately.

32
00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:06.965
<i>To trap me. make sure
I could never go back to you.</i>

33
00:01:13.206 --> 00:01:14.206
Fuck!

34
00:01:15.875 --> 00:01:16.908
It was a deer.

35
00:01:16.943 --> 00:01:18.509
It was a deer!

36
00:01:22.382 --> 00:01:23.748
Alison. if I don't do something.

37
00:01:23.783 --> 00:01:25.249
They're gonna convict me.

38
00:01:25.285 --> 00:01:27.552
<i>I know. just...
Just tell the truth.</i>

39
00:01:27.587 --> 00:01:29.354
Your honor.

40
00:01:29.389 --> 00:01:30.989
I'm guilty.
I killed scott lockhart.

41
00:01:31.024 --> 00:01:33.324
What the hell are you doing?
Sit down.

42
00:03:50.530 --> 00:03:52.196
Ready to go?

43
00:04:31.771 --> 00:04:33.504
Hey.

44
00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:36.507
Hi. Hey.

45
00:04:56.429 --> 00:04:58.396
How are you feeling?

46
00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:02.900
I'm fine.

47
00:05:14.514 --> 00:05:17.148
Thou preparest a table before me.

48
00:05:17.183 --> 00:05:19.951
In the presence of mine enemies.

49
00:05:19.986 --> 00:05:22.653
Thou anointest my head with oil.

50
00:05:22.689 --> 00:05:25.122
My cup runneth over.

51
00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:28.259
Surely goodness and mercy
shall follow me.

52
00:05:28.294 --> 00:05:30.428
All the days of my life.

53
00:05:30.463 --> 00:05:33.731
And I will dwell in the house
of the lord forever.

54
00:05:35.435 --> 00:05:37.602
We will conclude
our service with a eulogy.

55
00:05:37.637 --> 00:05:39.503
I now invite arthur's son.

56
00:05:39.539 --> 00:05:41.105
Noah solloway.

57
00:05:41.140 --> 00:05:44.742
To share some remembrances
of his beloved father.

58
00:05:55.955 --> 00:05:57.355
Um...

59
00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:09.767
Those of you who knew my dad
will... will know.

60
00:06:09.802 --> 00:06:12.637
That we didn't always
get along so well.

61
00:06:15.875 --> 00:06:17.875
But I-i loved him.

62
00:06:20.647 --> 00:06:22.847
I did love him.

63
00:06:22.882 --> 00:06:26.517
Wh-when I was a boy...

64
00:06:26.552 --> 00:06:28.519
He used to take me fishing
in the... in the lake.

65
00:06:28.554 --> 00:06:32.123
Behind the house
where we grew up. and...

66
00:06:39.165 --> 00:06:41.966
Well.
we both really enjoyed that.

67
00:06:42.001 --> 00:06:44.302
My sister was...

68
00:06:46.339 --> 00:06:47.705
She and my dad were very close.

69
00:06:47.740 --> 00:06:52.410
I think she was...
She was more his type.

70
00:06:54.447 --> 00:06:55.680
But then she left.

71
00:06:55.715 --> 00:06:56.715
Heh.

72
00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:09.160
That was a hard time.

73
00:07:11.464 --> 00:07:13.731
That was a hard time.

74
00:07:13.766 --> 00:07:16.500
He had a... he had a hard life.
At least I think he did.

75
00:07:16.536 --> 00:07:19.904
To be... to be honest.
I-i never really knew him.

76
00:07:22.375 --> 00:07:24.175
Um...

77
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:29.113
I always wanted to ask
more questions.

78
00:07:29.148 --> 00:07:31.015
You always think
there's gonna be...

79
00:07:31.050 --> 00:07:35.019
more time. but...

80
00:07:53.172 --> 00:07:54.972
Thank you for coming.

81
00:07:59.412 --> 00:08:03.414
Thank you. mr. Solloway.
for those. um. words.

82
00:08:03.449 --> 00:08:06.751
We will now conclude our service
by singing. at his request.

83
00:08:06.786 --> 00:08:08.753
Arthur's favorite song.

84
00:08:08.788 --> 00:08:11.756
"take me out to the ball game."

85
00:08:13.292 --> 00:08:14.959
Thank you for telling
that story. estelle.

86
00:08:14.994 --> 00:08:16.227
It was beautiful.

87
00:08:21.033 --> 00:08:22.600
I'm sorry.

88
00:08:22.635 --> 00:08:25.269
What is the matter with you?

89
00:08:25.304 --> 00:08:27.271
Nothing.

90
00:08:27.306 --> 00:08:28.973
Hey. there's your dad.

91
00:08:29.008 --> 00:08:30.474
Hey.

92
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.176
Hey. Thanks for coming.

93
00:08:32.211 --> 00:08:34.278
I think granddad
would have liked that.

94
00:08:34.313 --> 00:08:36.447
Short and sweet. No bullshit.

95
00:08:36.482 --> 00:08:38.449
Hel... helen.
thank you so much for coming.

96
00:08:38.484 --> 00:08:39.750
You didn't have to do that.

97
00:08:39.786 --> 00:08:41.419
Well. I knew your father
for 30 years.

98
00:08:41.454 --> 00:08:43.254
And you know. where else
would I be?

99
00:08:43.289 --> 00:08:45.289
Can I talk to you for a second?

100
00:08:48.394 --> 00:08:50.161
Come here. sweetie.

101
00:08:54.167 --> 00:08:55.800
You haven't returned
any of my calls.

102
00:08:55.835 --> 00:08:56.634
I know.

103
00:08:56.669 --> 00:08:58.803
Why not?

104
00:08:58.838 --> 00:08:59.703
I don't know.

105
00:08:59.739 --> 00:09:01.372
I... we need to talk.

106
00:09:01.407 --> 00:09:03.174
About what?
About what we're doing.

107
00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:05.743
About what our new arrangement's
going to be.

108
00:09:08.648 --> 00:09:09.858
Are you still living
at your sister's?

109
00:09:09.882 --> 00:09:10.714
Yes.

110
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:11.549
Well. will you be getting.

111
00:09:11.584 --> 00:09:12.383
A place of your own?

112
00:09:12.418 --> 00:09:13.784
Eventually.

113
00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:14.863
Do... i don't...
Don't you want someplace.

114
00:09:14.887 --> 00:09:16.387
Where you can be with the kids?

115
00:09:16.422 --> 00:09:18.456
They can come to nina's.
I mean alone.

116
00:09:18.491 --> 00:09:20.202
I don't think they want
to be alone with me.

117
00:09:20.226 --> 00:09:22.293
That's ridiculous.
You're their father.

118
00:09:22.328 --> 00:09:24.495
Stacey's afraid of me.
She's not afraid of you.

119
00:09:24.530 --> 00:09:27.531
She's uncomfortable 'cause she
hasn't seen you in three years.

120
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:31.001
That's why you need
to spend time with her.

121
00:09:31.037 --> 00:09:32.636
Okay. I'm trying. I swear I am.

122
00:09:32.672 --> 00:09:34.071
It's just... it's... it's been...

123
00:09:34.106 --> 00:09:35.306
It's been two months.

124
00:09:35.341 --> 00:09:37.508
Just give me a break. will ya?

125
00:09:44.450 --> 00:09:45.983
Um...

126
00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:49.887
What about us?

127
00:09:51.557 --> 00:09:52.857
What about us?

128
00:10:01.567 --> 00:10:03.100
Excuse me.

129
00:10:03.135 --> 00:10:03.934
Here.

130
00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:05.703
We got it.

131
00:10:11.244 --> 00:10:14.845
"Everyone the father gives to me
will come to me."

132
00:10:14.881 --> 00:10:18.349
I will never turn away
anyone who believes in me.

133
00:10:18.384 --> 00:10:20.351
He who raised Jesus christ
from the dead.

134
00:10:20.386 --> 00:10:22.720
Will also give new life
to our mortal bodies.

135
00:10:22.755 --> 00:10:24.221
Through his indwelling spirit.

136
00:10:25.591 --> 00:10:27.525
My heart. therefore. is glad.

137
00:10:27.560 --> 00:10:30.528
And my spirit rejoices.

138
00:10:30.563 --> 00:10:33.964
My body also shall rest in hope.

139
00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:36.433
You will show me
the path of life.

140
00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:39.136
In your presence
there is fullness of joy.

141
00:10:39.171 --> 00:10:42.706
"And in your right hand
are pleasures forevermore."

142
00:10:46.145 --> 00:10:48.579
noah!

143
00:10:48.614 --> 00:10:50.080
Noah!

144
00:10:55.354 --> 00:10:56.354
Noah!

145
00:11:05.698 --> 00:11:07.342
"The lord lift up
his countenance upon him.

146
00:11:07.366 --> 00:11:09.166
And give him peace."

147
00:11:09.201 --> 00:11:10.134
Amen.

148
00:11:10.169 --> 00:11:12.603
Amen.

149
00:11:12.638 --> 00:11:14.038
Amen.

150
00:11:39.732 --> 00:11:41.699
Thank you so much for coming.

151
00:11:49.075 --> 00:11:50.441
Thanks. Yes. of course.

152
00:11:50.476 --> 00:11:53.010
Thank you.

153
00:11:53.045 --> 00:11:54.011
You okay?

154
00:11:54.046 --> 00:11:55.813
That was a lovely service. nina.

155
00:11:55.848 --> 00:11:58.349
Your father would be pleased.
Thanks.

156
00:11:58.384 --> 00:12:00.362
You're coming back to the house.
though. aren't you?

157
00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:01.952
I don't know.

158
00:12:01.988 --> 00:12:03.687
Come on.

159
00:12:03.723 --> 00:12:05.689
The kids. they haven't
seen each other in forever.

160
00:12:05.725 --> 00:12:07.224
Mine are so looking forward
to it.

161
00:12:07.259 --> 00:12:09.693
Do you think we should
come back to the house?

162
00:12:09.729 --> 00:12:11.228
Only if you want to.

163
00:12:16.702 --> 00:12:18.669
It's a school night. so...

164
00:12:18.704 --> 00:12:21.505
right.

165
00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:23.040
This one time.

166
00:12:23.075 --> 00:12:24.341
Their grandfather just died.

167
00:12:24.377 --> 00:12:25.809
The... the kids
should be together.

168
00:12:25.845 --> 00:12:27.511
Nina. she gave her answer.

169
00:12:29.949 --> 00:12:32.349
We should go. Okay.

170
00:12:32.385 --> 00:12:34.429
Martin needs more time
with his homework this semester.

171
00:12:34.453 --> 00:12:36.353
Because he's been coming home
with cs and ds.

172
00:12:36.389 --> 00:12:38.055
