210
00:15:06.505 --> 00:15:08.038
It was fine.

211
00:15:08.073 --> 00:15:09.973
You have any fun?

212
00:15:10.009 --> 00:15:11.208
Not really.

213
00:15:12.945 --> 00:15:15.712
That's not the point. is it?
The point is to have a job.

214
00:15:15.748 --> 00:15:18.849
Well. if they like you.

215
00:15:18.884 --> 00:15:21.051
Then... Maybe they'll give you.

216
00:15:21.086 --> 00:15:23.654
A full-time gig
at the end of the semester.

217
00:15:23.689 --> 00:15:25.022
Maybe.

218
00:15:27.860 --> 00:15:29.593
You should really
shave that beard.

219
00:15:29.628 --> 00:15:30.628
You look insane.

220
00:15:34.567 --> 00:15:37.367
Noah. it's a good university.

221
00:15:37.403 --> 00:15:38.869
And you're a convict.

222
00:15:38.904 --> 00:15:40.304
Ex-convict.

223
00:15:42.041 --> 00:15:44.441
Don't you think
that's part of the appeal?

224
00:15:50.816 --> 00:15:53.784
I'm sorry. I'm just...

225
00:15:53.819 --> 00:15:55.586
I'm having a hard time.

226
00:15:55.621 --> 00:15:59.423
Of course you're having
a hard time.

227
00:15:59.458 --> 00:16:02.960
But it's... it's going
to get better.

228
00:16:02.995 --> 00:16:04.127
You just have to stay...

229
00:16:04.163 --> 00:16:05.729
Alive?

230
00:16:05.764 --> 00:16:07.965
I was going to say "positive."

231
00:16:17.476 --> 00:16:19.910
I think jp's tired of
having me around.

232
00:16:19.945 --> 00:16:21.979
Forget jp. I'll take care of it.

233
00:16:22.014 --> 00:16:24.414
He's just tired in general.

234
00:16:24.450 --> 00:16:26.650
It's just been a long summer.

235
00:16:34.793 --> 00:16:38.362
You know. you're the only one
who's every forgiven me. nin.

236
00:16:41.467 --> 00:16:43.467
<i>Well. you forgave me once.</i>

237
00:16:43.502 --> 00:16:46.136
For something
pretty awful. so...

238
00:16:51.810 --> 00:16:54.011
Besides.
I think you're innocent.

239
00:16:59.718 --> 00:17:01.551
I'm not.

240
00:18:14.026 --> 00:18:15.170
<i>How could he never mention it?</i>

241
00:18:15.194 --> 00:18:16.493
<i>What?</i>

242
00:18:16.528 --> 00:18:17.861
<i>You should have asked him.</i>

243
00:18:17.896 --> 00:18:19.563
<i>What is the matter with you?</i>

244
00:18:19.598 --> 00:18:20.742
<i>I would have never
asked him that.</i>

245
00:18:20.766 --> 00:18:22.265
<i>Just calm down.</i>

246
00:18:22.301 --> 00:18:24.401
<i>We're gonna figure it out. okay?</i>

247
00:18:24.436 --> 00:18:26.937
<i>What do you think
we're gonna do. nina?</i>

248
00:18:26.972 --> 00:18:29.039
<i>How do you think we're
gonna pay for this trip?</i>

249
00:18:29.074 --> 00:18:30.574
<i>And for christmas?</i>

250
00:18:30.609 --> 00:18:32.209
<i>It's got to be
some kind of joke.</i>

251
00:18:32.244 --> 00:18:34.745
<i>Your brother?
Your fucking brother?</i>

252
00:18:37.883 --> 00:18:39.483
Everything okay?

253
00:18:42.221 --> 00:18:44.788
Your father's will arrived
this morning.

254
00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:52.896
Okay.

255
00:18:55.434 --> 00:18:57.434
He didn't have much to leave.

256
00:18:59.304 --> 00:19:01.605
He had his house...

257
00:19:01.640 --> 00:19:04.041
Which he left to you.

258
00:19:04.076 --> 00:19:05.275
To me?

259
00:19:07.079 --> 00:19:08.278
Why?

260
00:19:08.313 --> 00:19:09.880
I don't know. noah.

261
00:19:09.915 --> 00:19:11.915
Why don't you tell us?

262
00:19:13.452 --> 00:19:15.452
I don't know either.

263
00:19:16.755 --> 00:19:18.255
You know he hated you?

264
00:19:18.290 --> 00:19:20.724
Jp. No. no. no.

265
00:19:20.759 --> 00:19:24.561
He could barely talk about you.

266
00:19:24.596 --> 00:19:26.129
She's the one.

