Dad left it to you.

305
00:21:08.066 --> 00:21:10.767
I'm never going back there.
nina.

306
00:21:10.802 --> 00:21:12.435
You know that.

307
00:21:14.306 --> 00:21:16.540
He was trying to apologize.

308
00:21:16.575 --> 00:21:18.542
Yeah. well.
it's too late for that.

309
00:21:20.045 --> 00:21:21.045
Fuckhead.

310
00:21:22.114 --> 00:21:24.714
It's way too late for that.

311
00:21:33.725 --> 00:21:35.692
"And so in the end.."

312
00:21:35.727 --> 00:21:37.894
As she watched him
get back into his car.

313
00:21:37.930 --> 00:21:40.597
And drive back
down the mountain.

314
00:21:40.632 --> 00:21:42.966
She couldn't help but wonder.

315
00:21:43.001 --> 00:21:45.402
Would she feel differently
in the morning?

316
00:21:45.437 --> 00:21:48.405
Would she wake up again
with that sense of possibility.

317
00:21:48.440 --> 00:21:51.808
That she'd taken for granted
as a girl?

318
00:21:51.843 --> 00:21:53.210
In other words.

319
00:21:53.245 --> 00:21:55.245
Is this moment the end
of her beginning.

320
00:21:55.280 --> 00:21:58.315
Or the beginning of her end?

321
00:21:58.350 --> 00:22:00.116
She was still
pondering the question.

322
00:22:00.152 --> 00:22:02.152
When she heard
the teakettle whistle.

323
00:22:02.187 --> 00:22:04.821
And turned from the window.

324
00:22:04.856 --> 00:22:08.091
"When she looked back again.
his car was gone."

325
00:22:09.861 --> 00:22:11.228
